Git and github me farq kya hai

Git aur GitHub ke beech ka antar samajhne ke liye aap ise aise maan sakte hain: Git ek software hai, aur GitHub us software ko istemal karne ka ek platform (website) hai.

Inhe vistar se samajhte hain:

1. Git (Version Control System)
Yeh kya hai? Git ek "Version Control System" (VCS) hai, jo aapke computer par locally install hota hai.

Iska kaam: Yeh aapke project ki files mein hone wale har badlav (changes) ko track karta hai. Agar aap code likh rahe hain aur galti se kuch bigad jaye, to Git ki madad se aap purane version par wapas ja sakte hain.

Kahan chalta hai? Yeh aapke apne computer (local machine) par chalta hai.

2. GitHub (Hosting Service)
Yeh kya hai? GitHub ek cloud-based platform hai jo Git ka istemal karta hai.

Iska kaam: Yeh ek aisi jagah hai jahan aap apna Git-based project internet par upload (push) kar sakte hain. Isse aap apne code ko backup kar sakte hain aur duniya bhar ke dusre developers ke saath milkar kaam kar sakte hain.

Kahan chalta hai? Yeh ek website (github.com) hai jo internet par chalti hai.

Ek Simple Example
Sochiye ki aap ek Kitab (book) likh rahe hain:

Git aapka "Save" button hai aur woh file jisme aap kitab likh rahe hain. Yeh track rakhta hai ki kal kaun sa paragraph likha tha aur aaj kya badla.

GitHub aapki kitab ka "Online Library" ya "Cloud Storage" hai, jahan aap apni kitab ko upload kar dete hain taaki koi aur bhi use padh sake ya usme sudhaar kar sake.

Mukhy Antar (Key Differences)
Feature	Git	GitHub
Prakar	Software/Tool	Website/Platform
Kahan hota hai?	Aapke Computer (Local)	Cloud (Internet)
Kaam	Files ka version manage karna	Code ko share aur store karna
Internet	Offline kaam kar sakta hai	Internet ki zaroorat hoti hai
Saar (Conclusion):
Aap Git ke bina GitHub istemal nahi kar sakte, kyunki GitHub ka kaam hi Git ki files ko sambhalna hai. Zyadatar developers apne computer par Git install karte hain aur apne projects ko backup aur collaboration ke liye GitHub par upload karte hain.

Kya aap apne kisi specific project ke liye Git ka istemal shuru karna chahte hain?

koi bhi project abhi me bana raha hu jese jese code likhu wese wese me github me upload karsakta hu and agar upload hone ke baad mene code me kuch update kiya to usko turant me upload kar ke new updated code github me dal sakta hu ?

and ye kese karu ?

Haan, bilkul! Aap apne code ko jaise-jaise likhte hain, waise-waise use GitHub par update kar sakte hain. Is process ko "Pushing" kehte hain.

Jab aap ek baar naya code update (edit) karte hain, to aapko sirf kuch commands chalani hoti hain aur aapka code turant GitHub par update ho jayega.

Iske liye aapko ye steps follow karne honge:

Step-by-Step Process
1. Setup (Sirf ek baar karna hai)
Apne computer par Git install karein.

GitHub par ek Repository banayein.

Apne folder mein terminal/command prompt kholein aur likhein:
git init (Ye aapke folder ko Git repository bana dega).
git remote add origin <GitHub_Repository_URL> (Ye aapke folder ko GitHub se jod dega).

2. Jab bhi aap code mein badlav (Update) karein
Jab aapne apna code likh liya ya kuch update kar diya, to GitHub par upload karne ke liye ye 3 commands chalaayein:

Changes ko stage karein:
git add .
(Iska matlab hai ki aapne jo bhi file edit ki hai, Git unhe select kar raha hai).

Changes ka note (Commit) likhein:
git commit -m "Yahan apne update ke baare mein likhein, jaise: Added new login feature"
(Isse Git ko pata chalta hai ki aapne kya badlav kiya hai).

GitHub par bhej dein:
git push origin main
(Isse aapka updated code aapke computer se GitHub par upload ho jayega).

Kya aapko baar-baar ye sab likhna hoga?
Haan, ye process hai. Lekin, pro tip ye hai:

VS Code (Editor) ka istemal karein: Agar aap VS Code use karte hain, to usme left side mein ek "Source Control" ka tab hota hai. Wahan aapko commands likhne ki zaroorat nahi padti; bas '+' button dabao (Add ke liye), message likho (Commit ke liye), aur 'Sync' button dabao (Push ke liye). Ye sab kaam ek-do clicks mein ho jata hai.

Kuch Zaroori Baatein:
Commit Message: Hamesha chhota aur clear message likhein taaki baad mein pata chale ki aapne kya update kiya tha.

Branching: Shuruat mein aap main branch par hi kaam karein, ye sabse asaan tareeka hai.

Frequent Commits: Zaruri nahi ki har ek line ke baad upload karein. Jab aapka koi chhota sa kaam (feature) pura ho jaye, tab push kar dein.

Kya aapne apne computer par Git install kar liya hai aur GitHub par repository bana li hai? Agar nahi, to bataiye, main aapko wahan se guide kar dunga.

pehle muje git install karna padega ? uske bina nahi ho sakta ?

Haan, agar aap chahte hain ki aapka code automatic tarike se sync (update) ho aur aap Version Control (purane code par wapas jana, alag-alag versions banana) ka sahi istemal kar sakein, to aapko Git install karna hi padega.

Bin Git install kiye GitHub ka use karne ka sirf ek hi tareeka hai, lekin woh "Manual" hai aur usme aapke kaam ki history track nahi hoti.

Bin Git install kiye GitHub kaise use karein (Manual Method)
Agar aap sirf files ko backup ke liye GitHub par rakhna chahte hain aur aapko Git ki advanced features nahi chahiye, to aap yeh kar sakte hain:

GitHub ki website par jayein.

Apni repository kholein.

"Upload files" button par click karein.

Apne computer se files drag-and-drop karke wahan daal dein.

Niche "Commit changes" button dabayein.

Is method ki kamiyaan:

Mehnat zyada hai: Har baar jab aap code mein ek chhota sa badlav karenge, aapko website par jaakar file delete karke nayi file upload karni padegi.

History nahi milegi: Aap yeh nahi dekh payenge ki aapne 1 ghante pehle kya code likha tha ya kaunsi line change ki thi.

Team mein kaam nahi kar sakte: Agar kabhi aap kisi aur ke saath milkar kaam karenge, to woh bahut mushkil ho jayega.

Git kyu zaroori hai? (Workflow ka diagram)
Git install karne se aapka computer aur GitHub ek "pipeline" se jud jaate hain. Aap apne computer par "Save" karte hain (Git), aur fir bas ek command (Push) se woh sara data GitHub par chala jata hai.

Meri Salah:
Agar aap programming mein serious hain aur aage badhna chahte hain, to Git install kar lena hi sabse behtar decision hai.

Ek baar ki mehnat: Git sirf ek baar install karna hota hai (5-10 minute ka kaam).

Professional skills: Industry mein har jagah Git hi use hota hai. Agar aap job ke liye interview denge, to Git ka knowledge hona mandatory hai.

Safety: Aapka code kabhi khoyega nahi, kyunki har chhota badlav save hota rehta hai.

Kya main aapki madad karun ye samajhne mein ki aapke operating system (Windows/Mac/Linux) ke hisaab se Git kaise download aur setup karein?

git kaha se install karu ?

Git install karna bahut simple hai. Aap ise official website se download kar sakte hain.

Git Kahan Se Download Karein?
Is link par jayein: https://git-scm.com/downloads

Installation Guide (Step-by-Step)
Select Your OS: Website par aapko apne Operating System (Windows, macOS, ya Linux) ke hisaab se button dikhega.

Download: Apne OS ke liye installer download karein.

Run Installer: Download hone ke baad file ko run karein.

Default Settings (Recommended): Installation ke dauran aapko bahut saare options dikhenge. Naye users ke liye "Next-Next-Next" karke default settings par hi install karna sabse sahi rehta hai. Isme sab kuch pehle se sahi set hota hai.

Finish: Installation complete ho jane ke baad, apne computer ko ek baar restart zaroor kar lein (taaki command prompt mein changes apply ho jayein).

Check Kaise Karein ki Install Hua Ya Nahi?
Install karne ke baad, check karne ke liye:

Apne computer par Command Prompt (CMD) ya Terminal kholein.

Yeh command type karein:
git --version

Enter dabayein. Agar aapko git version 2.x.x jaisa kuch dikh raha hai, toh iska matlab hai ki Git sahi se install ho gaya hai!

Ek Zaroori Setup (Configuration)
Jab aap pehli baar Git install karte hain, toh Git ko batana padta hai ki aap kaun hain (taaki GitHub par pata chale ki code kisne likha hai). Terminal mein ye do commands zaroor chalayein:

git config --global user.name "Aapka Naam"

git config --global user.email "apka-email@example.com" (Wahi email use karein jo aapne GitHub account ke liye rakha hai).

Ab jab Git install ho gaya hai, kya aap chahte hain ki main aapko pehla repository setup karne ka process bataun?

mene git isntall kar diya and woh ek terminal jesa open hua hai

Bahut badhiya! Agar aapne "Git Bash" open kiya hai, to aapne sahi cheez install ki hai. Ye bilkul terminal jaisa hi hota hai, jahan se hum saari Git commands run karenge.

Ab aap apne project ko GitHub se connect karne ke liye ready hain. Chaliye, ise 3 simple steps mein complete karte hain:

Step 1: Apne Folder ko Git Repository banayein
Sabse pehle apne computer mein us folder par jayein jahan aapka project rakha hai.

Us folder ke andar Right-click karein aur "Git Bash Here" select karein. (Ya phir terminal mein cd command use karke us folder tak jayein).

Ab ye command type karein:
git init
(Isse Git ko pata chal jayega ki aapko is folder ka track rakhna hai).

Step 2: GitHub se link karein
GitHub par jaakar ek nayi "Repository" banayein. Wahan aapko ek URL milega (jo https://github.com/aapka-username/repository-name.git jaisa hoga). Use copy karein.

Ab terminal mein ye command likhein:
git remote add origin <Woh-Copy-Kiya-Hua-URL>

Step 3: Apna pehla "Upload" (Push) karein
Ab har baar jab aap koi naya code likhenge, to ye 3 commands use karni hongi:

Sab files ko select karein:
git add .

Ek message ke saath save karein:
git commit -m "Mera pehla update"

GitHub par bhej dein:
git push -u origin main

Ek Zaroori Advice (Authentication)
Jab aap pehli baar git push karenge, toh GitHub aapse Login maangega.

Agar terminal mein password maange, toh aapko apna GitHub password nahi, balki "Personal Access Token" use karna pad sakta hai (GitHub aajkal security ke liye password ki jagah token leta hai).

Agar aap VS Code use kar rahe hain, toh wo aapko browser mein redirect kar dega, jahan aap bas "Authorize" button dabakar login kar sakte hain—ye sabse aasaan tareeka hai!

Kya aap abhi kisi specific project folder mein ye try kar rahe hain, ya koi error aa raha hai?

https://github.com/Aman-p02/veridoc_ai aesa url mila mene ek new repo create ki to

Bahut acche! Aapne bilkul sahi URL banaya hai. Yeh https://github.com/Aman-p02/veridoc_ai aapki nayi repository (repo) ka address hai.

Ab aapka agla kadam hai apne local folder (computer wala folder) ko is repo se link karna aur apne code ko wahan bhejna. Aapne jo Git install kiya hai, use ab is repository ke saath aise connect karein:

Step 1: Apne Computer ke Folder mein Setup karein
Apne computer mein us folder ko kholein jahan aapka project hai, aur phir wahan Git Bash open karein. Phir ye commands ek-ek karke chalayein:

Repository initialize karein:
git init

GitHub repo ko link karein:
git remote add origin https://github.com/Aman-p02/veridoc_ai.git
(Is command se Git ko pata chal gaya ki aapka code is specific URL par bhejna hai).

Branch ka naam 'main' set karein:
git branch -M main

Step 2: Pehla Code Upload (Push) karein
Ab jab bhi aap apna code pehli baar upload karenge, ye 3 commands chalayein:

Sab files ko staging area mein daalein:
git add .

Changes ko commit (save) karein:
git commit -m "First commit - project shuruat"

Code ko GitHub par bhej dein:
git push -u origin main

Kuch Zaroori Tips:
Authentication: Jab aap git push karenge, toh ho sakta hai GitHub aapka Username aur Password (ya Token) maange. Agar aap VS Code use kar rahe hain, toh wo aapko browser mein login karne ke liye bolega, jo sabse aasaan tareeka hai.

Verification: Ek baar push ho jaye, toh apne browser mein https://github.com/Aman-p02/veridoc_ai ko refresh karke dekhein. Aapka code wahan dikhne lagega!

Kya aapka code push ho gaya ya koi error aaya? Agar koi error dikh raha hai (jaise "Authentication failed" ya "Permission denied"), toh mujhe bataiye, main use fix karne mein aapki madad karunga.



