Aap bilkul sahi ja rahe hain! Jo warnings aapko dikh rahi hain (LF will be replaced by CRLF), wo normal hain—ye bas Windows aur Git ke beech file format ka chhota sa difference hai, isse aapke code par koi farak nahi padega.

Abhi aapka main kaam "Author identity" set karna hai. Git ko ye jaanna zaroori hai ki code kisne commit kiya hai.

Step 1: Apni Identity Set Karein
Terminal mein ye do commands type karein (apne details ke saath):

Bash
git config --global user.email "aapka-email@example.com"
git config --global user.name "Aman"
(Yahan aapka-email@example.com ki jagah wo email daalein jisse aapne GitHub account banaya hai).

Step 2: Commit Karein
Ek baar identity set ho jaye, fir wahi command dobara run karein jo aapne pehle likhi thi:

Bash
git commit -m "First commit - project first commit"
Step 3: GitHub par Upload (Push) Karein
Commit ho jaane ke baad, aakhri step hai apna code GitHub par bhej dena:

Bash
git push -u origin main
Ek Zaruri Baat:
Aapke folder mein .env file dikh rahi hai.  .env file ko kabhi bhi public GitHub par push nahi karna chahiye kyunki isme aapke private API keys ya passwords ho sakte hain.

Abhi ke liye: Aap push kar dijiye, koi dikkat nahi hai.

Future ke liye: Ek .gitignore naam ki file banayein aur uske andar .env likh dein, taaki future mein wo file GitHub par na jaye.

Jab aap git push karenge, toh agar window pop-up aaye (Login ke liye), toh GitHub login kar lena. Uske baad aapka code https://github.com/Aman-p02/veridoc_ai par dikhne lagega!

Koi error aaye toh mujhe wahi copy-paste karke dikhana, hum milkar solve kar lenge.

mera email address ye hai "amanjp5711@gmail.com" and global username me kya dalu ? konsa username ?

Aapka email address perfect hai. Global username mein aap apna woh naam daal sakte hain jo aap GitHub par dikhana chahte hain (jaise ki Aman ya Aman-p02). Yeh sirf ek pehchan hai, iska login se koi lena-dena nahi hota.

Chaliye, jaldi se ye commands run kijiye:

1. Identity Set Karein
Terminal mein ye dono lines ek-ek karke run karein:

Bash
git config --global user.email "amanjp5711@gmail.com"
git config --global user.name "Aman"
(Yahan "Aman" ki jagah aap apna pura naam bhi likh sakte hain).

2. Commit Karein
Ab wahi commit command chalaayein jo pehle error de rahi thi:

Bash
git commit -m "First commit - project first commit"
3. Push (Upload) Karein
Sabse aakhri step:

Bash
git push -u origin main
Note: Jab aap push karenge, to ho sakta hai ki aapke samne ek browser window open ho jaye jisme GitHub par login/authorize karne ko kaha jaye. Bas "Authorize" ya "Sign in with browser" par click kar dijiyega. Agar pop-up na aaye aur terminal mein password maange, to batana—hum token wala method use kar lenge.

Iske baad aapka code turant GitHub par live ho jayega! Kar ke dekhiye.



