Yeh error isliye aa raha hai kyunki jab aapne GitHub par nayi repository banayi thi, toh shayad aapne "Add a README file" ya "Add .gitignore" ya "License" waale box par tick kar diya tha.

Iska matlab hai ki GitHub par wo files pehle se hain, jo aapke computer wale folder mein nahi hain. Git ko lag raha hai ki aapka local code aur GitHub ka code alag-alag hain, isliye wo overwrite karne se mana kar raha hai.

Isse fix karne ka sabse asaan tareeka hai "Pull" karna:

Fix kaise karein:
Terminal mein ye command chalaayein:

Bash
git pull origin main --rebase
Yeh kya karega? Yeh GitHub ki un files ko (jo aapke folder mein nahi hain) aapke local folder mein download kar lega aur aapke code ke saath merge kar dega.

Uske baad wapas Push karein:
Jab pull successfully ho jaye, tab apna code wapas bhejiye:

Bash
git push -u origin main
Agar ye bhi error de:
Agar git pull karne par kuch conflict aaye (jo ki chances kam hain), toh aap force push bhi kar sakte hain (lekin dhyan rakhein, sirf tabhi jab aapko pata ho ki GitHub par koi aisi file nahi hai jo aapko bachani hai):

Bash
git push -u origin main --force
Ek important baat:
GitHub par agar koi README.md file bani hai, toh wo aapke local folder mein aa jayegi. Aap use apne VS Code mein dekh sakte hain.

Ab ek baar git pull karke check kariye, phir push ho jana chahiye. Kya hua?



