Aapke error ka karan "GitHub Push Protection" hai.

GitHub bahut smart hai—usne aapki .env file mein ek GCP API Key detect kar li hai. Security ke liye, GitHub aisi sensitive files ko public repository par upload nahi hone deta. Yeh ek bahut acchi feature hai, taaki aapka private data chori na ho.

Ise solve karne ke liye aapko ye steps karne honge:

Step 1: .env file ko Git se hatayein
Sabse pehle, aapko Git ko batana hoga ki wo .env file ko ignore kare.

Apne project folder mein ek nayi file banayein jiska naam ho: .gitignore

Is file ke andar sirf ye ek word likhein aur save kar dein:

.env

    *(Ab Git `.env` file ko kabhi upload nahi karega).*

### Step 2: Purani Commit se `.env` ko remove karein
Kyunki aapne pehle hi commit kar diya hai, `.env` aapki Git history mein abhi bhi hai. Ise hatane ke liye ye command chalayein:

```bash
git rm --cached .env
git commit -m "Remove sensitive .env file from git"
Step 3: Wapas Push karein
Ab try karein, is baar GitHub aapko block nahi karega:

Bash
git push -u origin main
Zaroori Salah (Important):
API Key Delete/Reset: Aapne jo API key apni .env file mein rakhi thi, ussey abhi ke abhi Google Cloud Console par jaakar "Revoke" ya "Delete" kar dein. Kyunki aapne use commit kar diya tha (bhale hi push nahi hua), isliye safe side par rehne ke liye nayi key generate karna behtar hota hai.

.env.example file: Log aksar .env ka ek copy banate hain jiska naam .env.example rakhte hain. Isme aap asli keys nahi daalte, bas template daalte hain (jaise: API_KEY=your_key_here). Aap ye file GitHub par push kar sakte hain, isse dusro ko pata chal jayega ki unhe kaunsi keys set karni hain.

Jab aap ye kar lenge, toh aapka code bina kisi error ke upload ho jayega!

text file banau ?

Haan, .gitignore file banana bahut zaroori hai. Isse aapka sensitive data (jaise API keys) kabhi public nahi hoga aur aapka project safe rahega.

Maine aapke liye ek standard .gitignore file content bana diya hai. Aap isse apne veridoc_ai folder mein .gitignore naam se save kar sakte hain:
TXT icon
gitignore
TXT

Is file ka istemal kaise karein?
Apne project folder (veridoc_ai) mein ek nayi text file banayein.

Usko rename karke .gitignore (bilkul yehi naam, aage dot zaroor lagana) rakh dein.

Upar di gayi file ka content copy karke usme paste kar dein aur save kar dein.

Iske baad, aap wahi commands chalayein jo maine pichli baar batayi thi:

Bash
git rm --cached .env
git add .
git commit -m "Add .gitignore and remove sensitive files"
git push -u origin main
Ek aur baat: Kyunki aapka project temp/ folder mein PDF files bhi use kar raha hai (jo shayad bahut badi ho sakti hain), agar wo files bahut zaroori nahi hain, to aap unhe bhi .gitignore mein daal sakte hain taaki Git ki speed achhi rahe.

Kya aapne .gitignore file bana li? Iske baad aapka code safely upload ho jayega!

