Aapne ek chhoti si galti kar di hai: aapne file ka naam .gitignore.txt rakha hai, jabki Git sirf .gitignore (bina .txt extension ke) naam ki file ko hi pehchanta hai. Isliye Git ne .env file ko ignore nahi kiya aur wo abhi bhi purani commit mein mojood hai.  
TXT

Isse puri tarah fix karne ke liye ye steps follow karein:

1. File ka naam sahi karein
Apne folder mein gitignore.txt file ka naam badalkar sirf .gitignore kar dein. (Agar Windows filename change karne mein dikkat de, toh VS Code mein "Rename" option use karein).

2. Git History se Purana Commit hatayein
Kyunki .env file aapki purani commit mein chali gayi hai, aapko pichli commit ko reset karna hoga taaki wo "saaf" ho jaye:

Bash
# Pichli commit ko undo karein (lekin aapka kaam folder mein hi rahega)
git reset --soft HEAD~1
3. Ab sab kuch sahi se add aur commit karein
Ab jab aapne .gitignore ka naam sahi kar diya hai, toh ye commands chalayein:

Bash
# Git ab .gitignore file ko dekhega aur .env ko ignore kar dega
git add .
git commit -m "Fresh commit with proper .gitignore"
4. Push karein
Ab finally push karein:

Bash
git push -u origin main
Zaroori Note:

Aapne jo gitignore.txt file banayi thi, uske content mein .env shamil hai, isliye ab GitHub aapko block nahi karega.  
TXT
+ 1

Agar aapne file ka naam .gitignore (sirf ye) rakh diya hai, toh GitHub aapke secret ko detect nahi kar payega kyunki wo file ab ignore ho chuki hogi.

Ek baar try kijiye, is baar definitely ho jana chahiye! Agar koi error aaye toh bas wahi terminal output yahan paste kar dena.

